Intro
There are two main ways to measure population using Census data: the
total population and the number of households. The Census Bureau
publishes more robust data on households, so this figure is more
commonly used for in-depth housing analysis. This post will explore
population and housing data for the city of Memphis, Shelby County, and
the Memphis MSA.
Population and Households
The following table shows the total population, number of households,
and average household size in Memphis, Shelby County, and the Memphis
Metro Area. Below each area are the 2020 estimates and the percent
change from 2010 to 2020.


